---
/**
 * Sub-processors list — required by DPA Annex 2 and customary for B2B SaaS.
 * Customers can subscribe to updates; 30 days' notice applies.
 */

import Legal from '../../layouts/Legal.astro';
---
<Legal
  title="Sub-processors"
  description="Current list of PartnerScope sub-processors, as referenced in our DPA."
  lastUpdated="2026-04-21"
>
  <p>
    This page lists the third parties ("sub-processors") that process personal data on behalf of
    PartnerScope in delivering the service. It forms Annex 2 to our Data Processing Addendum
    (<a href="/legal/dpa">/legal/dpa</a>) and is kept up to date.
  </p>

  <h2>Current sub-processors</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Sub-processor</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Data categories</th>
        <th>Location</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Stripe Payments Europe, Ltd.</td>
        <td>Payment processing for Starter, Pro, and Enterprise orders</td>
        <td>Name, email, billing address, VAT ID, payment token</td>
        <td>Ireland (EU); card network partners globally</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Resend Inc.</td>
        <td>Transactional email delivery (order confirmations, reports, internal intake)</td>
        <td>Name, email address, message body</td>
        <td>United States (SCCs + supplementary measures)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Hetzner Online GmbH <span class="legal-placeholder">{'{{TO CONFIRM BEFORE LAUNCH}}'}</span></td>
        <td>Application, database, and file hosting</td>
        <td>All categories processed by the PartnerScope platform</td>
        <td>Germany (Nuremberg / Falkenstein data centres)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Cloudflare, Inc.</td>
        <td>DNS, edge caching, WAF, and DDoS protection for partnerscope.eu</td>
        <td>IP address, request metadata; no assessment payloads</td>
        <td>Global edge (SCCs + EU Data Boundary configuration)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Sentry (Functional Software, Inc.)</td>
        <td>Application error and performance monitoring</td>
        <td>Stack traces, request metadata; PII scrubbed in-flight</td>
        <td>United States (SCCs)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>sevDesk GmbH <span class="legal-placeholder">{'{{TO CONFIRM BEFORE LAUNCH}}'}</span></td>
        <td>Invoice issuance and bookkeeping</td>
        <td>Name, company, billing address, VAT ID, line-items</td>
        <td>Germany (Offenburg)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>
    Customers on Pro and Enterprise tiers receive 30 days' prior notice of planned additions or
    replacements via the email address on file. To be added to the notification list at any
    tier, email <a href="mailto:privacy@partnerscope.eu">privacy@partnerscope.eu</a>.
  </p>

  <div class="legal-note">
    Entries marked <code>{'{{TO CONFIRM BEFORE LAUNCH}}'}</code> reflect the intended production
    sub-processors; they are confirmed once the contracts are signed. Keep this page under
    change-control — an out-of-date sub-processor list can itself be a GDPR violation in audit.
  </div>
</Legal>
